{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:17:55.594Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":"I now have full context. Let me write the review.\n\n## Spec Review: KB-006\n\n### Verdict: APPROVE\n\n### Summary\nThis is a thorough, well-structured specification that was revised to fix the critical `siteUrl` parameter gap in structured data helper function signatures. The updated spec now correctly passes `siteUrl` to `generateMusicAlbumSchema` and `generateMusicRecordingSchema","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:17:56.223Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":"`, uses proper schema.org `EPRelease` enumeration values, and includes helpful notes about the OG image dimension caveat. All steps have concrete, verifiable outcomes with real automated tests.\n\n### Issues Found\n1. **[Severity: minor]** — `resolveAbsoluteUrl` doesn't handle `siteUrl` with a trailing slash. The spec says `Astro.site.href` is the source for `siteUrl`. In Astro, `","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:17:58.665Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":"Astro.site.href` returns a URL **with** a trailing slash (e.g., `https://sam.music/`). The current `resolveAbsoluteUrl` logic is `${siteUrl}${path.startsWith('/') ? '' : '/'}${path}`, which would produce `https://sam.music//images/releases/foo.svg` (double slash) when `siteUrl` has a trailing slash and `path` starts with `/`. The spec","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:00.490Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" should note that the function needs to strip a trailing slash from `siteUrl` or handle the concatenation edge case. This is a real bug that would surface during implementation but is straightforward to fix.\n\n### Criteria Assessment\n- **Mission clarity:** Clear and precise. The mission statement describes exactly what to build (SEOHead component, structured data helpers, sitemap, robots.txt) and why (search discoverability + rich social","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:02.052Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" previews).\n- **Step specificity:** Excellent. Every step has concrete checkboxes with specific values — function signatures, field mappings, test cases with expected inputs/outputs, HTML elements to verify in `dist/`. Step 5 even names exact files to inspect (`dist/releases/midnight-sessions/index.html`).\n- **File scope accuracy:** Accurate and complete. All 5 new files and 6 modified files are listed.","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:04.841Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" Cross-references to KB-002 files (`BaseLayout.astro`, `astro.config.mjs`) and KB-004 files (`config.ts`, `[slug].astro`, `ReleasesLayout.astro`) are consistent with what those specs would produce.\n- **Dependency correctness:** Correct. Both KB-002 (scaffolding) and KB-004 (release pages + content schema) are necessary and sufficient prerequisites. The","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:06.988Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" dependency descriptions accurately list what each provides.\n- **Testing requirements:** Strong. Steps 1 and 2 each require dedicated test files with enumerated test cases. The structured data tests are pure TypeScript (no Astro test framework needed). The SEOHead test acknowledges the Astro component testing challenge and offers a pragmatic fallback (extract logic to pure TS helper). Step 5 requires build output inspection as a final quality gate.\n- **Documentation completeness:** Complete. \"Must Update\" (README.md with SEO section) and \"Check If Affected\" (BaseLayout.astro prop interface) are both present and appropriate.\n- **Sizing & review level:** Appropriate. Size S and Review Level 1 (Plan Only) are correct — this task adds a component, a helper module, a static file, and a config change to an existing project, all well-under","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:09.869Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":"stood patterns.\n\n### Suggestions\n- The `resolveAbsoluteUrl` helper should explicitly handle trailing-slash normalization on `siteUrl` (strip trailing `/` from `siteUrl` before concatenation) since `Astro.site.href` returns `https://sam.music/`. Consider adding a test case for this in the test spec: e.g., `resolveAbsoluteUrl(\"/images/foo.svg\", \"https://sam.music/\")`","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:11.452Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" should produce `https://sam.music/images/foo.svg` (not `https://sam.music//images/foo.svg`).\n- The spec could note that `SEOHead.astro` should import `resolveAbsoluteUrl` from `../scripts/structured-data.ts` — the component uses this helper for `og:image` resolution (Step 2 says \"resolve to absolute URL using `resolveAbsoluteUrl`\") but doesn't explicitly state","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:13.220Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" the import. Minor, since the worker would naturally figure this out.\n- Step 3's `[slug].astro` modification should also consider that `ReleasesLayout.astro` (from KB-004) wraps `BaseLayout.astro`. The SEO props need to flow through `ReleasesLayout` → `BaseLayout` → `SEOHead`. The spec says to modify `[slug].astro` to pass props","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:18:14.654Z","taskId":"KB-006","text":" \"to layout\" but doesn't explicitly call out updating `ReleasesLayout.astro` to forward SEO props. If `ReleasesLayout` passes props through to `BaseLayout`, this works; if it renders `BaseLayout` with hardcoded props, it would need modification. This should be verified during implementation (the preflight check would catch it).","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
